The paper focuses on software engineering tasks related to mining change patterns from Git repositories, which falls under the scope of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The tool Coming uses XML to specify change patterns, which suggests a possible connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions analyzing fine-grained changes between revisions, which could be related to cs.SD (Software Development). Additionally, the evaluation of the tool involves finding instances of change patterns, which could be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
